%N A128426 Decimal expansion of the location of a maximum of a Fibonacci Hamiltonian function.
%C A128426 The abscissa x of a unique maximum of the f(x) in Theorem 1 of Damanik et al., arising in spectrum of a periodic operator of the one-dimensional Schrodinger equation.
%C A128426 The value of f(x) at the maximum is A091648.
%H A128426 David Damanik, Mark Embree, Anton Gorodetski, and Serguei Tcheremchantsev, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s00220-008-0451-3">The Fractal Dimension of the Spectrum of the Fibonacci Hamiltonian</a>, Communications in Mathematical Physics, Vol. 280, No. 2 (2008), pp. 499-516; <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/0705.0338">arXiv preprint</a>, arXiv:0705.0338 [math-ph], 2007. See p. 501 (p. 3 in the preprint).
%F A128426 Equals 2*(6 - sqrt(2))/17.
%e A128426 0.53950428677963587661156603244591787310945036760271...
%t A128426 RealDigits[2*(6 - Sqrt[2])/17, 10, 120][[1]] (* _Amiram Eldar_, Mar 26 2026 *)
